    "Discrepancy measures the difference between the expected (uniform) distribution and the actual distribution of points within a given space.",
    "A lower discrepancy means that the actual distribution of points is closer to the uniform distribution.",
    "Thus, having less discrepancy means points are more diverse.There are different ways to calculate QMC.",
    "In this research, L 2 -star measure is used [22].",
    "To calculate QMC discrepancy with L 2 -star measure, the d-dimensional hypercube is conceptually subdivided into smaller subcubes of equal size."
